    "what_description": "Nitrosalsola portilloi is a succulent plant species endemic to Chile, belonging to the family Amaranthaceae. It is characterized by its small, leafless stems covered with tiny, scale-like leaves that protect the plant from water loss. Nitrosalsola portilloi exhibits greenish-white flowers in terminal panicles, which are rich in nitrate. The plant's leaves are absent due to the adaptation to arid environments, and its stems are capable of storing water. Nitrosalsola portilloi grows up to 30 centimeters in height and thrives in areas with high salinity and low rainfall.",
