    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Nitrosalsola portilloi are anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, antimicrobial, and antidiabetic. Its anti-inflammatory property is attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids, which have been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines and enzymes. Antioxidant activity is exhibited by the plant's ability to scavenge free radicals, thereby protecting cells from oxidative damage, a function attributed to the bioactive compounds saponins and volatile oils. Additionally, Nitrosalsola portilloi has been found to possess antimicrobial properties, effective against a range of microorganisms, including bacteria and fungi, due to the presence of alkaloids and glycosides. Furthermore, the plant's antidiabetic property is attributed to the bioactive compounds phytosterols and phenolic acids, which have been shown to increase insulin sensitivity and glucose uptake in cells.",
