    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Nitrosalsola portilloi are tea, infusion, tincture, salve, and decoction. These preparations are made by infusing the plant's leaves and stems in hot water to create a tea or infusion, which is rich in antioxidants and has antimicrobial properties. A tincture is made by steeping the plant in a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin to extract its bioactive compounds, which can be used to treat various health conditions. A salve is made by infusing the plant in oil to create a topical ointment that can be used to treat skin conditions such as wounds and inflammation. Decoction involves boiling the plant's woody parts in water to release its bioactive compounds, which can be used to treat digestive issues and other health conditions.",
